<HEADLINE>
FT  10 JUL 93 / Finance and the Family: Age Concern's capital book - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Age Concern England has published a book Using Your Home as Capital for
those seeking to raise money from their house. The book covers the main
options and is suitably harsh on the ones which have caused investors
problems in the past.
For example, under the heading 'Investment Bond Income Schemes', the authors
write 'These schemes are not recommended under any circumstances' and their
advantages are described as 'nil'. Written by Cecil Hinton and David
Bookbinder, the book is available for Pounds 4.50 from Dept UHC, Age Concern
England, 1268 London Road, London SW16 4ER.
