</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANIES in the north are confused about economic recovery, with no
consistent pattern of improvement yet apparent, according to the Yorkshire
and Humberside regional council of the Confederation of British Industry.
Mr Brian Bigley, CBI regional director, said: 'Order books are better than
they were three, six and nine months ago, but it seems half a step back for
every step forward.'
