FT  09 JUL 93 / London may get EC drug test base
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government's campaign to have the European Medicines Evaluation Agency
based in London received a boost yesterday when the Medicines Control Agency
said a third of all new applications for drug licences in the European
Community were being handled in the UK.
Mrs Virginia Bottomley, health secretary, said the strengths of the UK
medicines regulatory system - its scientific excellence, speedy and
efficient licensing and commitment to protecting public health - were
evident.
