FT  09 JUL 93 / Parliament and Politics: Tony Blair calls for new sense of
direction for Labour
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL CASSELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR must champion a new relationship between society and the individual
which embraces public intervention but safeguards individual freedoms, Mr
Tony Blair, shadow home secretary, said last night, Michael Cassell writes.
Mr Blair said the party must grasp the ideological initiative and provide a
lead for a country which had lost its sense of purpose and direction.
Giving the tenth Arnold Goodman charity lecture, Mr Blair said he wanted to
see 'a new concept of citizenship in which rights and responsibilities go
together and where we cease to posit an entirely false choice between social
and personal responsibility'.
The purpose of economic and social policy, he said, should be to extend
opportunity, remove the underlying causes of social alienation and also take
tough measures to ensure that chances extended to people were taken up.
