FT  09 JUL 93 / Hyundai peace talks resume
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARK NICHOLSON and JOHN BURTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SEOUL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Workers at Hyundai, South Korea's largest conglomerate, resumed partial
walkouts yesterday after staging a one-day general strike as negotiations
began again between labour and management over a pay agreement, writes John
Burton from Seoul.
But the Hyundai trade unions warned industrial action could escalate again
if the government intervened with a show of force. The South Korean
government indicated it would not prosecute trade union officials for the
illegal strike action if they displayed flexibility in negotiating with
Hyundai.
